Text:
To create a graph using Mermaid.js that reflects your requirements, you'll need to follow the syntax for defining nodes and connecting them appropriately. Below is an example of how you can structure this data into a graph using Mermaid's `graph TD` (top-down) syntax. This example assumes some placeholder data for each category:

```mermaid
graph TD

  classDef entity fill:#ADD8E6,stroke:#000;
  classDef attribute fill:#FFFFFF,stroke:#000;
  classDef relation fill:#FFA500,stroke:#000;
  classDef goal fill:#90EE90,stroke:#000;
  classDef condition fill:#FF6347,stroke:#000;
  classDef decisionVariable fill:#9370DB,stroke:#000;

  subgraph Entities
    E1[E1]:::entity
    E2[E2]:::entity
  end

  subgraph Attributes
    A1[A1]:::attribute
    A2[A2]:::attribute
    A3[A3]:::attribute
  end
  
  subgraph Relations
    R1[R1]:::relation
    R2[R2]:::relation
  end

  subgraph Goals
    G1[G1]:::goal
    G2[G2]:::goal
  end
  
  subgraph Conditions
    C1[C1]:::condition
    C2[C2]:::condition
  end
  
  subgraph DecisionVariables
    DV1[DV1]:::decisionVariable
    DV2[DV2]:::decisionVariable
  end

  // Connect Entities with their Attributes
  E1 -.-> A1
  E1 -.-> A2
  E2 -.-> A3

  // Connect Entities with their Relations
  E1 --> R1
  E2 --> R2

  // Connect Goals with Entity/Attributes
  G1 -.-> E1
  G1 -.-> A1
  G2 -.-> E2

  // Connect Conditions with Entity/Attributes
  C1 -.-> E1
  C1 -.-> A2
  C2 -.-> E2

  // Connect DecisionVariables with their relevant Entities
  DV1 --> E1
  DV2 --> E2

```

### Explanation:

- **Entities** are represented by `E1`, `E2` and colored in blue.
- **Attributes** such as `A1`, `A2`, `A3` are connected to the entities they belong to, shown in white.
- **Relations** like `R1`, `R2` connect between entities and are orange.
- **Goals** (`G1`, `G2`) connect to either entities or attributes and are green.
- **Conditions** (`C1`, `C2`) link with entities or attributes and are red.
- **Decision Variables** (`DV1`, `DV2`) directly relate to the relevant entities and appear in purple.

Adjust node names and connections as per your actual data. This structure provides a visual representation of how these different components interact within your system using Mermaid.js. You can paste this code into the Mermaid Live Editor to visualize it.
